-- Commodities Are More Preferred by Investors, Morgan Stanley Says From Poll
-- B y   C l a u d i a   C a r p e n t e r
-- 2010-10-01T06:28:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/commodities-are-more-preferred-by-investors-morgan-stanley-says-from-poll.html
Commodities are becoming a more
preferred asset by investors in the past three months, according
to a survey by Morgan Stanley.  Commodities scored 24 percent of the vote as the preferred
global asset class for the next 12 months, compared with zero in
June, Morgan Stanley said in a report today. The preferred
global asset for the next 12 months is equities at 53 percent,
down from 74 percent in June, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  